The search for one of the two people who drowned in South beach on Wednesday (5 February) continues. Provincial police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala said today (Tuesday), 11 February that since Thursday, (6 February), search and rescue teams have been actively going into the sea in an attempt to recover the body of the man who is still missing after he and his two friends faced difficulties while swimming. One swimmer managed to swim to the shore to get help. “The woman who was part of the group managed to swim back to shore and alerted authorities that two of her friends had drowned. The lifeless body of one man was found 100m away from where they had drowned and there is only one that is still missing,” said Gwala. Police said that an inquest docket was opened and the search continues.